    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-kitten-sasl-saml-ec-20.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-kitten-sasl-saml-ec-20.txt</link>
        <title>"SAML Enhanced Client SASL and GSS-API Mechanisms", Scott Cantor, Margaret Cullen, Simon Josefsson</title>
        <dc:date>2021-05-10T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML) 2.0 is a generalized framework for the exchange of security-related information between asserting and relying parties.  Simple Authentication and Security Layer (SASL) and the Generic Security Service Application Program Interface (GSS-API) are application frameworks that facilitate an extensible authentication model, among other things.  This document specifies a SASL and GSS-API mechanism for SAML 2.0 that leverages the capabilities of a SAML-aware "enhanced client" to address significant barriers to federated authentication in a manner that encourages reuse of existing SAML bindings and profiles designed for non-browser scenarios.</description>
    </item>
